,"name": "Banana Banana Bread"
,"aggregateRating": {
"@type": "AggregateRating",
"ratingValue": "4.7",
"ratingCount": "17340"
}
,"cookTime": "PT60M"
,"keywords": "publisher-tested"
,"nutrition": {
"@type": "NutritionInformation"
,"calories": "231 kcal"
,"carbohydrateContent": "35 g"
,"cholesterolContent": "51 mg"
,"fiberContent": "2 g"
,"proteinContent": "4 g"
,"saturatedFatContent": "5 g"
,"sodiumContent": "226 mg"
,"sugarContent": "16 g"
,"fatContent": "9 g"
,"unsaturatedFatContent": "0 g"
}
,"prepTime": "PT15M"
, "recipeCategory": ["Breakfast","Brunch"]
,"recipeCuisine": ["American"]
,"recipeIngredient": [
"2 cups all-purpose flour",
"1 teaspoon baking soda",
"0.25 teaspoon salt",
"0.75 cup brown sugar",
"0.5 cup butter",
"2 eggs, beaten",
"2.3333332538605 cups mashed overripe bananas" ]
,"recipeInstructions": [
{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Ob3CnHnJ4dGfr16X2TiMYclokMc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-016-step-01-264370503a9c4031bb4515c3e79ffb89.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x5-inch loaf pan."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/tRWMaL5y8Ttzso7mV48oIlsm6hQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-017-step-02-97801d682d8b455f975aae6dec856837.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Combine flour, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl. Beat brown sugar and butter with an electric mixer in a separate large bowl until smooth. Stir in eggs and mashed bananas until well blended. Stir banana mixture into flour mixture until just combined."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/KA7Snkx0dEd9tKo8sKlWZBRpMvY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-018-step-03-c14df521f62848dbabccb19d8c232a2e.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Pour batter into the prepared loaf pan."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Dk3RKD2UZ1q4BmYeMxqFFinbnAw=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-019-step-04-971aa588a15644d0a836a267ba205216.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 60 minutes."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/hzmgq7xuWSOJgVyTHVo-50AI2Js=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-020-step-05-25918e9fd077418ab2eb854c67ec8ac2.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Let bread cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/fAkQn-FhjF89oTJ5JXpgwvwNf34=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/20144-banana-banana-bread-VAT-009-4x3-B-78f1cfc64bfa451e8a0fead814719b9f.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Enjoy!"
} ]
,"recipeYield": ["12", "1 (9x5-inch) loaf"]
,"totalTime": "PT75M"
,"review": [
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "SOULWOLF"
}
,
"reviewBody": "I've made several banana bread recipes here and I always come back to this one, it is a wonderful standard recipe that you can build upon and customize to your liking. A few pointers... This is a DENSE bread, the last one I made I actually weighed on my kitchen scale and it came to just under 2 1/2 lbs! This probably due to the 2 1/3 cups mashed bananas; I generally use about 5 medium size bananas but have used a little as three and it still came out good. If you like a lighter cake or muffin type bread, look elsewhere. Mix the ingredients carefully; I use my mixer to cream the butter and sugar and incorporate the eggs, but for the bananas and flour mixture I use a wooden spoon and mix gently until everything has just come together. I also add about 3/4 to 1 cup of chopped walnuts. 350 degrees for 1 hour, 15 minutes works for me but it is extremely important that I watch where my oven racks are positioned, too high in the oven and the bottom will not bake correctly, too low and it burns before the middle it cooked through. I position my rack one notch lower than direct middle of my oven and it comes out perfectly. Test with a toothpick in several places for doneness so you don't mistakenly hit a banana piece and think it is underdone. I think that's it!"
},
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Allrecipes Member"
},
"reviewBody": "Excellent recipe!! I added 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts and brushed the top with a mixture of 1tbs water and 3 tbs brown sugar for a sweet crunch on top.",
"datePublished": "2002-11-01T09:03:07.717Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Michael Brenner"
},
"reviewBody": "Excellent recipe, I did add a dash of cinnamon and a teaspoon of vanilla. I also made it a 2nd time and put it in an 8 x 8 glass baking dish and topped with a crumb topping( 1 cup flour 6 tbs butter, 1 cup brown sugar and a tsp cinnamon.) Next will be crumb topped muffins.",
"datePublished": "2024-10-28T21:51:26.252Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "WorthyCrisp9577"
},
"reviewBody": "This is by far the best banana bread I've ever made. As per a user suggestion, I added in 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to give it a more fall-flavor, but I'm sure it could be left out and still taste amazing. I baked it in a mini multi-loaf pan (with 6 loaves) for 20 minutes and it came out perfect. My husband and 8 year old cannot get enough! A definite keeper.",
"datePublished": "2024-10-08T15:13:33.876Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "wilramos"
},
"reviewBody": "Very easy &amp; tasty, I add a tsp of Nutmeg and Vanilla, the walnuts were a great added flavor. I also brushed the top with a 1 tsp. water and 2 tsp. Brown sugar that put a perfect sweet crunch on the top.",
"datePublished": "2024-12-14T05:54:01.879Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Jen"
},
"reviewBody": "My favorite thing to do to Banana Nut Bread is to add chopped pecans, lightly sprinkled with Sanding Sugar (King Arthur Baking) to the top AND bottom of the bread. I do so by adding both ingredients first to the bottom of a loaf pan that has been lightly sprayed with Pam, then to the top of the batter just before going in the oven. It offers a lightly sweet and crunchy texture to the already delicious bread. So good!",
"datePublished": "2024-11-05T15:13:32.790Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Arleen Tempesco McCoy"
},
"reviewBody": "Great recipe for ripe bananas, I added a banana extra for extra moist bread! Also added a teaspoon of vanilla and 3/4 cup of walnuts! For the top, crumpled a tablespoon of butter into 1/2 cup of brown sugar and a teaspoon of cinnamon, crumpled on top! So yummy",
"datePublished": "2025-01-12T15:24:04.140Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "JumpyTongs3296"
},
"reviewBody": "This is the third time I made this banana bread. Yes, it is indeed a keeper. I used almond flour, coconut flour, and this time Bob's Red Mill Gluten Free All-Purpose Baking Flour and it came out really great! I also added sliced almonds. I am so pleased with the outcome. I doubled the recipe and baked it in Pamper's Chef baking pan. It cooked exactly for an hour as you stated in the recipe. I divided into three, decorated with sliced heart-shaped hearts and gave it to two of my good friends as my Valentine's Day card for them and they love it! Thank you very much for this recipe.",
"datePublished": "2025-02-15T06:04:46.860Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Valerie Hoffman"
},
"reviewBody": "I love this recipe and wanted to make it at our place off the grid (no mixer). So I melted the butter and brown sugar in a saucepan and stirred till incorporated, like caramel. I let it cool just a bit before I added the eggs and bananas. I followed the rest of the recipe as written. Sometimes I add vanilla just because so many baked goods recipes call for vanilla. It came out perfect. I now make it the same way at home without a mixer. It's such a great tasting, easy recipe with minimal ingredients. Very moist.",
"datePublished": "2026-04-11T22:10:20.634Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "4"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Slacker"
},
"reviewBody": "Made this gluten free with Bob's 1 to 1 GF baking flour and 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts. Also added 1 Tsp of baking powder, 3/4 Tsp of nutmeg and 1 TSP of cinnamon. It took 65 minutes at 350 to fully cook. Came out really good and better than other recipes that use 1/2 cup or more of vegetable oil.",
"datePublished": "2025-02-08T21:44:21.514Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Ancient Mariner"
},
"reviewBody": "DEFINITELYY made a bunch of changes, due to ingredients-on-hand and also due to the fact I'm a unorthodox rebel. First off, I didn't use my oven, I used my propane bbq, (don't laugh, it works). Next, I had no flour, only pancake batter. Used NO butter, as 2 eggs has plenty of fat. 1/2 cup golden monkfruit, instead of brown sugar. Added 1/4 cup of shreded coconut, walnuts, and 3 RIPE bananas. Also, a tablespoon of vanilla, &amp; a teaspoon of cinnamon. Grilled in the loaf pan for exactly 60 minutes, then cooled-it-down for an hour. I nearly fainted it was so good. Light, fluffy, perfectly sweet!",
"datePublished": "2025-07-18T21:29:32.757Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Robert Yee"
},
"reviewBody": "Chocolate Chips and dried cranberries or raisins.",
"datePublished": "2026-06-10T01:50:07.240Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
